properties.description:
PREPARE TO LEAVE: Sunshine Acres bushfire as at 2.20pm Thur 4 Feb        Bushfire warning level: WATCH AND ACT     Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) advises there is a bushfire in Sunshine Acres and conditions could get worse.    You need to  be ready to follow your bushfire survival plan . If you do not have a plan, or intend to leave, you should  be ready to leave the area because the situation could get worse quickly .    Currently as at 2.20pm Thursday 4 February a fast-moving bushfire is travelling in the vicinity of Baxters Road, Sunshine Acres and Black Swamp Creek. The fire is likely to impact Sunshine Acres, as well as Corella Way, Honeyeater Drive and Finch Court, Walligan. Maryborough Hervey Bay Road is closed in both directions.    Fire crews are working to contain the fire but firefighters may not be able to protect every property. You should not expect a firefighter at your door.    People in the area will be affected by smoke, which will reduce visibility and air quality.    Call Triple Zero (000) immediately if you believe your property is under threat. 
Response Time: 20210204132309
